---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Terms of service — appelsin"
	description="The terms under which you can use appelsin.io for your event."
>
	<div class="flex min-h-screen flex-col">
		<header class="flex items-start justify-between px-8 pt-6 sm:px-12 sm:pt-8">
			<a href="/" aria-label="appelsin.io home" class="block">
				<img src="/logo.svg" alt="appelsin.io" width="110" height="110" />
			</a>
			<nav class="flex items-center gap-3 pt-4 text-sm sm:text-base">
				<a href="/login" class="text-zinc-100 hover:text-orange-400">Login</a>
				<span class="text-zinc-400">|</span>
				<a href="/terms" class="text-orange-400">Terms</a>
				<span class="text-zinc-400">|</span>
				<a href="/privacy" class="text-zinc-100 hover:text-orange-400">Privacy</a>
			</nav>
		</header>

		<main class="mx-auto w-full max-w-3xl px-6 pb-24 pt-8 sm:px-12">
			<h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-white sm:text-4xl">
				Terms of service
			</h1>
			<p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">Last updated: 18 May 2026</p>

			<p class="mt-6 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				These terms govern your use of <strong>appelsin.io</strong>
				(“appelsin”, “we”). By creating an account or paying for an event,
				you agree to them. If you don’t, please don’t use the service.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">1. What appelsin does</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				appelsin lets event hosts collect photos from their guests via a QR
				code and display them live on a screen at the venue. After the event
				we keep the photos for the period stated in your chosen plan, then
				delete them.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">2. Your account</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				You must be 18 or older to create a host account. You are
				responsible for keeping your login link confidential and for
				everything that happens under your account.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">
				3. Your responsibilities as host
			</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				When you create an event you become the
				<strong>controller</strong> of the guest photos collected through it
				under the GDPR. That means you are responsible for:
			</p>
			<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				<li>
					displaying a clear notice at the venue — typically on the printed
					QR cards — explaining what appelsin is, that uploaded photos may
					appear on the live display, and that you will receive them after
					the event;
				</li>
				<li>handling any guest request to remove their photo;</li>
				<li>
					having a lawful basis to display recognisable people on the
					screen — usually guest consent at the moment of upload.
				</li>
			</ul>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				appelsin acts as your <strong>processor</strong> in this
				relationship. A Data Processing Agreement is available on request.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">4. Acceptable use</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				You and your guests will not upload:
			</p>
			<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				<li>
					content that is illegal, infringes a third-party right, depicts
					minors in private settings, or is otherwise non-consensual;
				</li>
				<li>malware, deceptive or abusive content;</li>
				<li>content intended to disrupt or attack the service.</li>
			</ul>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				We may remove content and suspend accounts for violations without
				prior notice.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">5. Payments</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				Event passes are one-off payments processed by Stripe. Prices are
				shown at checkout. Because an event pass unlocks a time-bound piece
				of functionality (your event date), it is non-refundable once the
				event status has changed to <em>live</em>. Before that, you can
				request a refund within 14 days at
				<a class="text-orange-400 underline hover:text-orange-300" href="mailto:hello@appelsin.io">hello@appelsin.io</a>.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">
				6. Photo content and licence
			</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				Your guests own the photos they upload. By using the service you and
				your guests grant appelsin a limited, non-exclusive licence to host,
				process, transcode and display the photos
				<strong>solely to deliver the service to you</strong>. We do not use
				guest photos to train models and we do not use them for marketing.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">7. Retention</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				Photos and event metadata are deleted automatically once the
				retention period of your plan expires (7, 30 or 90 days after the
				event end, depending on the tier). Host account data is deleted on
				request or 12 months after your last activity.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">8. Availability</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				We aim for high availability but provide the service “as is”. We do
				not guarantee uninterrupted service. To the maximum extent permitted
				by law, our liability for any claim arising from your use of the
				service is capped at the amount you paid for the affected event.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">9. Termination</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				You can stop using the service at any time. We may suspend or delete
				an account that violates these terms. Once an event is paid for and
				<em>live</em>, we will let it run to its scheduled end barring
				serious abuse.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">10. Changes</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				We may update these terms. Material changes will be announced by
				email to active hosts at least 14 days before they take effect.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">11. Governing law</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				These terms are governed by the laws of Denmark. Disputes shall be
				brought before the competent Danish courts, without prejudice to any
				mandatory consumer-protection rules in your country of residence.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">12. Contact</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				<a class="text-orange-400 underline hover:text-orange-300" href="mailto:hello@appelsin.io">hello@appelsin.io</a><br />
				[Legal entity name], CVR [number]<br />
				[Postal address], Denmark
			</p>
		</main>
	</div>
</Layout>
